Citation.sTitle: Excess molar volumes, excess molar enthalpies, and excess isentropic compressibilities of tetrahydropyran with aromatic hydrocarbons
Citation.sAbstract: Excess molar volumes, excess molar enthalpies, and speeds of sound, data of {tetrahydropyran (i) + benzene, or toluene, or o-, or p-, or m-xylene (j)} binary mixtures have been measured as a function of composition at a temperature of 308.15 K. Speeds of sound data have been utilized to predict excess isentropic compressibilities, The excess properties data for the investigated mixtures have been analyzed in terms of the Graph theory which in turn deals with topology of the constituents of mixtures. An analysis of excess molar volume data in terms of Graph theory suggests that these mixtures are characterized by interactions between dipole of tetrahydropyran and p-electron cloud of aromatic ring of aromatic hydrocarbons to form 1:1 molecular complex. It has been observed that the excess properties values predicted by the Graph theory compare well with their corresponding experimental values.
